<br>
Wizards are the car that gets from 0-60 faster than any other car, but burns fuel faster and takes 125,000 miles of seasoning, plus a ton of accessories added to the car to get there.  Further, the car is poor on corners and the suspension is so stiff it breaks if it hits a pothole.  Other cars can reach 60 faster until it gets to this 125,000 mile mark and has all the accessories added to it, on a straightaway.  But it has a bitchen stereo.<br>
<br>
Rogues are the car that gets from 0-60 nearly as fast as Wizards, with the best accessories, but gets there with only about 4,000 miles of seasoning, corners well, and has a very solid but flexible suspension.  Further, the suspension is computer reactive, so that if they do run into poor terrain, the car can adjust and survive the potholes.  Rogues have a nice garage door opener, but they don't have a nice stereo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueliathen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliathen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/4/01 7:30:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee dmg v caster dmg.</span><hr size=1> I'll take the stereo thanks.  ..seriously, I would. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grimicon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/4/01 8:40:31 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.kestrelarts.com/images/grim3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Melee dmg v caster dmg.</span><hr size=1> Yeah.  Problem is this game is more an autorace than just tooling around meeting girlies and enjoying your tunes.  If the game had more depth and more TO it than it does, sure that would be great.  But it doesn't. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhiraghm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hiraghm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffff